grade: Jōyō kanji, taught in junior high
on reading compounds: 軒【ケン】counter for buildings (esp. houses), suffix for a pen name, stage name, etc.
軒昂【ケンコウ】high-spirited, being in high spirits
一軒一軒【イッケンイッケン】house to house, door to door
kun reading compounds: 軒【のき】eaves, narrow aisle surrounding the core of a temple building
軒並み【のきなみ】row of houses, every house, each house, every door, all, totally, altogether, across the board
